title.narrative: Scholarships and Training for Egyptian Professionals (STEP)

description.narrative: (Egypt): Through this program, USAID will continue to provide scholarships for women for Master's in Business Administration (MBA) and undergraduate degrees in the fields of science, technology, engineering, math (STEM) and business administration to study in the United States. Currently, there are 98 MBAs and 62 undergraduates in STEM fields. The program also provides training, study tours, and technical assistance to improve the capacity of key academic, private sector, and government organizations with the aim of creating a cadre of highly-trained female leaders in the STEM fields and business administration.
